# Code Readability

## No Magic Numbers

Replace bare literals with named constants.

```gdscript
# BAD
if health < 25:
    speed = speed * 0.5

# GOOD
const LOW_HEALTH_THRESHOLD = 25
const WOUNDED_SPEED_MULTIPLIER = 0.5

if health < LOW_HEALTH_THRESHOLD:
    speed = speed * WOUNDED_SPEED_MULTIPLIER
```

```csharp
// BAD
if (health < 25) speed *= 0.5f;

// GOOD
const int LowHealthThreshold = 25;
const float WoundedSpeedMultiplier = 0.5f;

if (health < LowHealthThreshold) speed *= WoundedSpeedMultiplier;
```

## Descriptive Variable Names

Single-character names are only acceptable for loop indices (`i`, `j`, `k`) and common math (`x`, `y`, `z`). All other variables must have meaningful names.

```gdscript
# BAD
var d = 0.0
var t = get_node("Timer")
func calc(a, b):
    return a + b

# GOOD
var distance = 0.0
var respawn_timer = get_node("Timer")
func calculate_damage(base_damage, multiplier):
    return base_damage * multiplier
```

## Language Idioms

Use the idiomatic patterns of the language in use.

**GDScript**
```gdscript
# Use @export, @onready, typed arrays, match instead of if/elif chains
@onready var sprite: Sprite2D = $Sprite2D

match state:
    State.IDLE: handle_idle()
    State.RUNNING: handle_running()
    _: push_error("Unhandled state: %s" % state)
```

**C#**
```csharp
// Use properties over public fields, pattern matching, LINQ where appropriate
public float MaxHealth { get; private set; }

if (node is Player player)
    player.TakeDamage(damage);
```

**Python**
```python
# Use list comprehensions, context managers, f-strings
names = [item.name for item in inventory if item.is_equipped]

with open(path) as file:
    content = file.read()
```

**Rust**
```rust
// Use ? over unwrap/expect for error propagation
fn load_config(path: &Path) -> Result<Config, AppError> {
    let content = fs::read_to_string(path)?;
    let config = toml::from_str(&content)?;
    Ok(config)
}

// Use iterators over manual loops
let active_names: Vec<String> = players
    .iter()
    .filter(|p| p.is_active)
    .map(|p| p.name.clone())
    .collect();

// Use type aliases to give meaning to primitives
type TrackId = u32;
type SampleRate = u32;

// Use match exhaustively — no catch-all _ unless truly unreachable
match event {
    Event::Play(track_id) => player.play(track_id),
    Event::Pause => player.pause(),
    Event::Stop => player.stop(),
}
```
